text: Chionodes dammersi is a moth in the family Gelechiidae. It is found in North America, where it has been recorded from California and Arizona.Chionodes at funetmothphotographersgroup The larvae feed on Eriogonum elongatum, Eriogonum inflatum, Eriogonum abrorescens, Eriogonum fasciculatum, Eriogonum grande, Eriogonum latifolium and Eriogonum parvifolium. ==References== Category:Chionodes Category:Moths described in 1936 Category:Moths of North America
title: Chionodes dammersi
